  "text": "for all φ ∈ ω ψ . As in [CITATION_1] , since we are considering a high enough lift, the arguments used in the proof of [39, Theorem I.2.2] allow us to conclude that H(g) ≡ 0. This forces all functions of the form (23) to vanish, and hence the density results force all functions of the form (24) to also vanish. However, it is a straightforward check to show that the non-vanishing of Fourier coefficients associated to O Θ,5m = (2 5m ) in Theorem 9.1 forces these Fourier coefficients associated to the orbit O = (2 4m 1 m ) to be non-vanishing for some choice of data. We therefore obtain a contradiction.",
